block content

    div.container
        h1.text-center= title
        h2.text-center= election_name

        div
            p Dear participant,

            p Thank you very much for taking part on this research project! Your involvement is highly appreciated. This survey will take approximately 10 minutes.

            p Before starting, PLEASE make sure you read this first and understand the voting mechanism!
            
            p You will be tasked to vote between statements using 2 different mechanisms. First you will vote under the classical 1-Person-1-Vote mechanism, where you will be able to select one of the given statements. Then you will vote under the Quadratic Voting mechanism. Here you will be given a limited number of tokens that you can spend to buy votes. 1 vote will cost you 1 token, 2 votes will cost you 4 tokens, 3 votes will cost you 9 tokens (this is the quadratic part). It is up to you how you want to distribute your budget to better reflect your preferences but remember that the votes get more expensive every time!

            h5 <b><u>1-P-1-V example:</u></b>
            
            p You are part of a schools committee and you must vote on a mascot. You are given the option to vote for something or against something. You are given the following options:
            ol            
              li A Monkey
              li A Donkey
              li A Dog
              li A Wildcat
              
            p Because you adore the Monkey, but hate the Wildcat, you have to decide to whether vote FOR the Monkey or AGAINST the Wildcat, so when you fill in your ballot it could look like this:
            table.table.table-borderless
                thead
                    th Animals
                    th Vote
                tbody
                    td Monkey
                    td 0
                tbody
                    td Donkey
                    td 0
                tbody
                    td Dog
                    td 0
                tbody
                    td Wildcat
                    td Against

            h5 <b><u>Quadratic Voting example:</u></b>
            p You are part of a schools sports committee and you must vote on a mascot. You are given 100 tokens to vote on the following options:
            ol            
              li A Monkey
              li A Donkey
              li A Dog
              li A Wildcat
            p You prefer the monkey, like the donkey, are indifferent towards the dog and absolutely hate the wildcat. Therefore, you allocate your tokens the following way:
            table.table.table-borderless
                thead
                    th Animals
                    th Tokens
                    th Vote
                tbody
                    td Monkey
                    td 36
                    td 6
                tbody
                    td Donkey
                    td 14
                    td 3.74
                tbody
                    td Dog
                    td 0
                    td 0
                tbody
                    td Wildcat
                    td -50
                    td -7.04

            p Note how big the difference in total votes between the monkey and the wildcat is in the end (-1.04), regardless of the 14 tokens difference!
                    
            p <u><b>Important Note:</b></u>
            p Please make sure to fill in as much information on the personal information section as possible, as this is going to be vital to analyze the results. You are more than welcome to pass your information on an anonymous basis and give a pseudonym instead of your real name. 
            p Thank you in advance and have fun!

        hr
        
        form(method="post", action="/election/vote")
            input(type="hidden", name="electionId", id="electionId", value=election_id)
            input(type="hidden", name="electionName", id="electionName", value=election_name)
            
            h4 Personal Info

            .form-row
                .form-group.col-md-6
                    label(for="inputAge") Age
                    input(type="Number", class="form-control", name="inputAge", id="inputAge", placeholder="", required)
		    
                .form-group.col-md-6
                    label(for="inputOrientation") Sexual Orientation
                    select(type="text", class="form-control", name="inputOrientation", id="inputOrientation", placeholder="Sexual Orientation", required)
                        option(disabled, selected, value) -- Select Orientation --
                        option(value="Other") Other
                        option(value="Homo") Lesbian/Gay
                        option(value="Hetero") Heterosexual
                        option(value="Bi") Bisexual
                        option(value="Unknown") I'd rather not say
            .form-row

                .form-group.col-md-6
                    label(for="inputOccupation") Occupation
                    select(type="text", class="form-control", name="inputOccupation", id="inputOccupation", placeholder="Occupation", required)
                        option(disabled, selected, value) -- Select Occupation --
                        option(value="Student") Student
                        option(value="Self-employed") Self-employed
                        option(value="Employed") Employed
                        option(value="Unemployed") Unemployed
                        option(value="Academia") Researcher/Scientist
			option(value="Other") Other
            .form-row
                .form-group.col-md-6
                    label(for="inputGender") Gender
                    select(type="text", class="form-control", name="inputGender", id="inputGender", placeholder="Gender", required)
                        option(disabled, selected, value) -- Select Gender --
                        option(value="Other") Other
                        option(value="Female") Female
                        option(value="Male") Male
                        option(value="Unknown") I'd rather not say

                .form-group.col-md-6
                    label(for="inputNationality") Nationality
                    select(class="form-control", name="inputNationality", id="inputNationality", placeholder="Nationality", required)
                        option(disabled, selected, value) -- Select Nationality --
                        +country-list

            hr
            
            .form-group
                h4 Do you identify with any of the following? (Check all that apply)

                .form-check
                    label.form-check-label
                        input.form-check-input.check(type="checkbox", value="woman", name="identity", style="margin-top:0px")
                        h6 Woman

                .form-check
                    label.form-check-label(for="migration")
                        input.form-check-input.check(type="checkbox", name="identity", id="migration", value="migration", style="margin-top:0px")
                        h6 Migration History

                .form-check
                    label.form-check-label(for="entrepreneur")
                        input.form-check-input.check(type="checkbox", name="identity", id="entrepreneur", value="entrepreneur", style="margin-top:0px")
                        h6 Entrepreneur

                .form-check
                    label.form-check-label(for="lgbt")
                        input.form-check-input.check(type="checkbox", name="identity", id="lgbt", value="lgbt", style="margin-top:0px")
                        h6 LGBTQI+

                .form-check
                    label.form-check-label(for="researcher")
                        input.form-check-input.check(type="checkbox", name="identity", id="researcher", value="researcher", style="margin-top:0px")
                        h6 Researcher

                .form-check
                    label.form-check-label
                        input.form-check-input.none-check(type="checkbox", name="identity", value="none", style="margin-top:0px", checked)
                        h6 None of the above

            hr
            
            .form-group
                h4 1 Person - 1 Vote (You can only choose <b>one</b>)
                each statement, index in statements
                    .form-row
                        .form-group.col-8
                            label= statement
                        .form-check.form-check-inline
                            - var yes_val = [index, statement, "Yes"]
                            input.form-check-input(type="radio", name="Vote1", id="Vote - " + statement + " Y", value=yes_val, required)
                            label.form-check-label(for="Vote - " + statement + " Y") Y
                        .form-check.form-check-inline
                            - var no_val = [index, statement, "No"]
                            input.form-check-input(type="radio", name="Vote1", id="Vote - " + statement + " N", value=no_val, required)
                            label.form-check-label(for="Vote - " + statement + " N") N

            hr

            h4 Quadratic Voting
            - var curr_tokens_txt = input_amount
            h5.text-center.font-weight-bold <u>Available Tokens: 
              span#curr_tokens #{curr_tokens_txt}
              span  / #{input_amount}</u>

            .div
                .row
                    .col-6
                        h6 <b>Statement</b>
                    .col-2
                        h6 <b>Tokens</b>
                    .col-2
                        h6 <b>Votes</b>

            each statement in statements
                .row
                    .form-group.col-sm-6
                        label= statement
                    .form-group.col-sm-2
                        input.quadratic-voter(type="number", name="QuadraticVote", class="form-control", placeholder="0", required)

                    .form-group.col-sm-2.votes-out
                        span.btn.votes 0


            button(type="submit", class="btn btn-primary") Submit

    script.
        
        $(".quadratic-voter").on('input', function () {
          var curr = $(this).val();

          if(!(isNaN(curr))) {
              
              var previous_val = $(this).data('previous-val');
              if(previous_val === undefined) {previous_val = 0;};
              
              var curr_val = $(this).val();

              var diff = Math.abs(curr_val) - Math.abs(previous_val);
              var curr_tokens = $('#curr_tokens').text();
              var new_tokens = curr_tokens - diff;

              if(new_tokens <= #{input_amount} && new_tokens >= 0) {
                  $(this).data('previous-val', curr_val);
                  $('#curr_tokens').text(new_tokens);

                  var votes = Math.sqrt(Math.abs(curr_val)).toFixed(2) * Math.sign(curr_val);
                  $(this).parent().parent().children('.votes-out').children('span').text(votes);
              } else {
                  $(this).val(previous_val);
              }
          }
        });

        $(".none-check").click(function() {
          if($(this).prop("checked") == true) {
              $('.check').prop('checked', false);
          }
        });

        $(".check").click(function() {
          if($(this).prop("checked") == true) {
              $('.none-check').prop('checked', false);
          }
        });

	
